Patch summary:
Turn Launcher3/Quickstep into the desktop shell. This consolidated patch owns
the user-facing desktop behavior: taskbar-first navigation, desktop app drawer
behavior, taskbar context menus, pinning and bubbles integration, freeform
window coordination, responsive device profiles, dynamic display refresh,
show-desktop plumbing, taskbar popup/live-bounds fixes, visual effects,
deep shortcuts, log cleanup, and tests for those interactions.

The guiding idea is that the taskbar is the primary desktop control surface.
The app drawer should open from the taskbar start button, context menus should
anchor to the item the user clicked, apps should work in freeform windows, and
layout should remain sane as the VM display changes shape.

